Some applications of recursion in file system manipulation.

(1)base method without recursion, get all the files and directories directly inside a given root.
(2)get all the files paths inside all levels of main directory and subdirectories for a given root path.
(3)recursively create a file inside all levels of main directory and subdirectories for a given root path.
(4)recursively delete a given file inside all levels of main directory and subdirectories for a given root path.

All working examples are given in the source.
